HEADWORD: Trihedral
<hw>Tri*he"dral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Trihedron</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>Having three sides or
faces; thus, a <xex>trihedral</xex> angle is a solid angle bounded by
three plane angles.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>triedral</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

